<TITLE> Germany keen to invest in gas, power, ship building </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 21 (bdnews24.com)--The German government has shown interest to invest in energy sector, happy with the government plans to resolve gas and electricity crises. Germany is seeing the government plans from a positive point of view, German ambassador Holger Michal told reporters after a meeting with finance minister A M A Muhith at the Secretariat. The finance minister has discussed the plans in detail and requested Germany to invest in this sector, he said, expressing the hope that his government will respond positively. Michal said German businesses are interested to invest in the fledgling shipbuilding industry. A team of 20-plus from different sectors of Germany will visit Bangladesh at the month-end to explore investment possibilities in those sectors and visit shipbuilding factories, said Michal. The government has taken a five-year plan to raise $10 billion in funds for the gas and power sector, of which $ 7 billion will be spent in production and $3 billion in supply. However, the government is yet to formally announce the plan. Later, a group of representatives from Bangladesh Paper Cone and Tube Manufacturers Association met with the minister.
